{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015q2En14WhdQT1PYaXBqk7A","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Phase 0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN fix-2 Review — codex gpt-5.4 verdict\n2\t\n3\tReviewer: `codex --model gpt-5.4 --sandbox read-only`.\n4\tTarget: branch `phase-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z` HEAD `f7343c8`.\n5\tBaseline: `277fa4c`. Commits under review: `14a4612`, `64c5d6e`, `f7343c8`.\n6\tCherry-pick: `0fa6710` on `main`.\n7\tReview log: `dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-fix-2-review-20260527T135041Z.log`.\n8\t\n9\t## Verdict: BLOCK\n10\t\n11\t### 1. [high] D4 still does not encode D3's \"unknown kind = error\" rule coherently\n12\tRefs: `dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md:287`, `:343`, `:138`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-schema/src/lib.rs:51`\n13\t\n14\tThe known `CASE` branches match D3. The fallback does not. D4 says `ELSE NULL` will raise `SQLITE_CONSTRAINT` via a NOT NULL check and roll the migration back, yet the same section later says vec0 metadata columns do not have declarative `NOT NULL` support and the migration surface is pure SQL. As written, the memo no longer proves that an unexpected legacy `kind` aborts the migration instead of inserting a `NULL source_type`, so D3 and D4 are still inconsistent on error behavior.\n15\t\n16\t### 2. [medium] The `<now>` backfill claim is tied to the wrong Rust anchor and introduces an unsupported mechanism\n17\tRefs: `dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md:243`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1119`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-schema/src/lib.rs:102`\n18\t\n19\tD4 says `<now>` is rendered when the migration array is constructed at `open_with_migrations`, but that anchor only accepts an already-built `&'static [Migration]`; the actual registry is the static `MIGRATIONS` table. If the design wants a uniform migration-time timestamp literal, it needs a supported construction path or a different anchor.\n20\t\n21\t### 3. [low] D8 still contains a stale proof point from the pre-fix-2 migration shape\n22\tRef: `dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md:570`\n23\t\n24\tCites an `INSERT INTO vector_default_v2 ... SELECT v.rowid` clause that no longer exists after the staged-copy rewrite. Rowid-preservation conclusion is still fine; the specific reference is stale.\n25\t\n26\t## Addressed\n27\t\n28\t- Fix-1 finding (rebuild_vec0 semantics) — FIXED.\n29\t- D3 lock — still intact.\n30\t- D6 secondary fixture — still fixed.\n31\t\n32\t## What passed\n33\t\n34\t- D4 core shape aligned with the requested staged-copy migration.\n35\t- `CASE` mapping consistent with D3 for known values.\n36\t- `_fathomdb_vector_rows.kind` JOIN consistent with writer contract.\n37\t- D1, D2, D5, D6, D7 still consistent.\n38\t\n39\t## Reviewer process notes\n40\t\n41\t- `MEMORY.md` / `feedback_*.md` absent from checkout.\n42\t\n43\t## Orchestrator triage\n44\t\n45\tDate: 2026-05-27. Third BLOCK. No override allowed. Fix-3 required and constrained to:\n46\t\n47\t- Finding 1: replace the `ELSE NULL` claim with a real fail-fast: add a pre-INSERT statement to the same migration SQL string that selects-counts unknown kinds and uses an expression that errors if the count is non-zero. Simplest pattern is a UNIQUE constraint violation forced via INSERT INTO a sentinel table; or use SQLite's `RAISE` inside a CTE constraint. The cleanest practical option: prefix the migration with `SELECT CASE WHEN EXISTS(SELECT 1 FROM _fathomdb_vector_rows WHERE kind NOT IN ('email','article','paper','meeting','note','todo','doc')) THEN RAISE_ABORT() ELSE 1 END;` where `RAISE_ABORT()` is implemented by a CHECK constraint or by an expression that throws (e.g., `json_error()` or division-by-zero). Pick a primitive that exists in SQLite + sqlite-vec 0.1.7 and cite it. Document any caveat (e.g., \"no RAISE outside triggers in vanilla SQL\"). The acceptable patterns include: pre-INSERT validation INSERT INTO a `_migration_assertion(check_passes INTEGER NOT NULL CHECK(check_passes = 1))` table with `SELECT (COUNT(*) = 0)` from the unknown-kind check. State the chosen pattern explicitly.\n48\t- Finding 2: drop the `<now>` rendering claim entirely. Use SQLite's `strftime('%s', 'now')` in the SQL — it evaluates to a uniform integer at INSERT time across all rows in a single statement. Pure SQL, no Rust rendering, no migration-construction time needed. Update D4 + remove anchor 1119.\n49\t- Finding 3: remove the stale `vector_default_v2` reference in D8 (paragraph at line ~570). Replace with the staged-copy proof (rowid is the explicit JOIN key in the staging INSERT; the recreated `vector_default` receives the same rowid in the repopulation INSERT — same conclusion, accurate citation).\n50\t\n51\tFix-3 prompt at `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-fix-3.md`. This is the last design-pass iteration; if codex BLOCKs again on substantive new findings vs nitpicks, orchestrator will escalate to user.\n52\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5e259876-f4b4-41bd-a27c-d31853bc06c1","uuid":"510468b3-897a-411a-a28c-450b67d68aa2","timestamp":"2026-05-27T13:55:13.204Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z/dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-fix-2-review-20260527T135041Z.md","content":"# Phase 0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN fix-2 Review — codex gpt-5.4 verdict\n\nReviewer: `codex --model gpt-5.4 --sandbox read-only`.\nTarget: branch `phase-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z` HEAD `f7343c8`.\nBaseline: `277fa4c`. Commits under review: `14a4612`, `64c5d6e`, `f7343c8`.\nCherry-pick: `0fa6710` on `main`.\nReview log: `dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-fix-2-review-20260527T135041Z.log`.\n\n## Verdict: BLOCK\n\n### 1. [high] D4 still does not encode D3's \"unknown kind = error\" rule coherently\nRefs: `dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md:287`, `:343`, `:138`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-schema/src/lib.rs:51`\n\nThe known `CASE` branches match D3. The fallback does not. D4 says `ELSE NULL` will raise `SQLITE_CONSTRAINT` via a NOT NULL check and roll the migration back, yet the same section later says vec0 metadata columns do not have declarative `NOT NULL` support and the migration surface is pure SQL. As written, the memo no longer proves that an unexpected legacy `kind` aborts the migration instead of inserting a `NULL source_type`, so D3 and D4 are still inconsistent on error behavior.\n\n### 2. [medium] The `<now>` backfill claim is tied to the wrong Rust anchor and introduces an unsupported mechanism\nRefs: `dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md:243`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1119`; `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-schema/src/lib.rs:102`\n\nD4 says `<now>` is rendered when the migration array is constructed at `open_with_migrations`, but that anchor only accepts an already-built `&'static [Migration]`; the actual registry is the static `MIGRATIONS` table. If the design wants a uniform migration-time timestamp literal, it needs a supported construction path or a different anchor.\n\n### 3. [low] D8 still contains a stale proof point from the pre-fix-2 migration shape\nRef: `dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md:570`\n\nCites an `INSERT INTO vector_default_v2 ... SELECT v.rowid` clause that no longer exists after the staged-copy rewrite. Rowid-preservation conclusion is still fine; the specific reference is stale.\n\n## Addressed\n\n- Fix-1 finding (rebuild_vec0 semantics) — FIXED.\n- D3 lock — still intact.\n- D6 secondary fixture — still fixed.\n\n## What passed\n\n- D4 core shape aligned with the requested staged-copy migration.\n- `CASE` mapping consistent with D3 for known values.\n- `_fathomdb_vector_rows.kind` JOIN consistent with writer contract.\n- D1, D2, D5, D6, D7 still consistent.\n\n## Reviewer process notes\n\n- `MEMORY.md` / `feedback_*.md` absent from checkout.\n\n## Orchestrator triage\n\nDate: 2026-05-27. Third BLOCK. No override allowed. Fix-3 required and constrained to:\n\n- Finding 1: replace the `ELSE NULL` claim with a real fail-fast: add a pre-INSERT statement to the same migration SQL string that selects-counts unknown kinds and uses an expression that errors if the count is non-zero. Simplest pattern is a UNIQUE constraint violation forced via INSERT INTO a sentinel table; or use SQLite's `RAISE` inside a CTE constraint. The cleanest practical option: prefix the migration with `SELECT CASE WHEN EXISTS(SELECT 1 FROM _fathomdb_vector_rows WHERE kind NOT IN ('email','article','paper','meeting','note','todo','doc')) THEN RAISE_ABORT() ELSE 1 END;` where `RAISE_ABORT()` is implemented by a CHECK constraint or by an expression that throws (e.g., `json_error()` or division-by-zero). Pick a primitive that exists in SQLite + sqlite-vec 0.1.7 and cite it. Document any caveat (e.g., \"no RAISE outside triggers in vanilla SQL\"). The acceptable patterns include: pre-INSERT validation INSERT INTO a `_migration_assertion(check_passes INTEGER NOT NULL CHECK(check_passes = 1))` table with `SELECT (COUNT(*) = 0)` from the unknown-kind check. State the chosen pattern explicitly.\n- Finding 2: drop the `<now>` rendering claim entirely. Use SQLite's `strftime('%s', 'now')` in the SQL — it evaluates to a uniform integer at INSERT time across all rows in a single statement. Pure SQL, no Rust rendering, no migration-construction time needed. Update D4 + remove anchor 1119.\n- Finding 3: remove the stale `vector_default_v2` reference in D8 (paragraph at line ~570). Replace with the staged-copy proof (rowid is the explicit JOIN key in the staging INSERT; the recreated `vector_default` receives the same rowid in the repopulation INSERT — same conclusion, accurate citation).\n\nFix-3 prompt at `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-fix-3.md`. This is the last design-pass iteration; if codex BLOCKs again on substantive new findings vs nitpicks, orchestrator will escalate to user.\n","numLines":52,"startLine":1,"totalLines":52}}}
